Key Match Events: Tyler Herro scored 23 points to lead the Miami Heat to a 97-92 victory over the Utah Jazz.
Jaime Jaquez Jr. added 20 points, including key free throws in the final moments.
Bam Adebayo contributed 15 points, seven rebounds, three assists, three steals, and two blocked shots.
Lauri Markkanen and Collin Sexton each scored 23 points for the Jazz.
Walker Kessler hauled in 15 rebounds for the Jazz.
Kyle Filipowski had 11 boards, two steals, and a block for the Jazz.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz lost their ninth consecutive game at the Delta Center.
Neither team shot well, with the Jazz making 39.8 percent of their shots and the Heat shooting 39.6 percent.
